The second DAIS Learnathon is held at CSBD (MPI-CBG) in Dresden from June 4th to June 8th, 2018.

= Preparation =
<ol>
  <li>Follow the Gitter channel for news: https://gitter.im/juglab/DaisLearnathon18</li>
  <li>Bring your laptop</li>
  <li>Make sure you have the following stuff installed:
    <ul>
      <li>Eclipse Oxygen (recommended for starters) or IntelliJ</li>
      <li>GIT</li>
      <li>Maven</li>
      <li>bash or zsh</li>
      <li>Miniconda or Anaconda
        <ul>
          <li>Install [https://conda.io/miniconda.html Miniconda] if you do not have installed it or Anaconda already. (We need the version for Python 3!)</li>
          <li>Your <code>.bashrc</code> or <code>.zshrc</code> has to include the path to your conda installation: <code>export PATH="/PATH_TO_INSTALLATION/miniconda3/bin:$PATH"</code></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>
In case you have problems preparing your system we can organize a software installation session on Sunday evening (June 4th). Please let us know by writing a mail to [mailto:frauzufall@mpi-cbg.de frauzufall@mpi-cbg.de].
